    <h1>About the ISS App</h1>
          <p>I made the ISS App because it's frickin' amazing that there's a satellite with people in it flying around the world at 17,000 mph conducting experiments to benefit mankind. There are a few apps out there that already track the ISS and alert you when it will be visible in the sky. Still, I want to try and create my own because it will give me a chance to learn a lot about Rails, the ISS, Google Maps APIs, how satellites move through orbit, and about cartography (much like Buster Bluth).</p>

